   f(x) = \begin{cases} x\cdot \sin \frac1x,&x\neq 0 \\ 0,&x = 0 \end{cases} 
a\neq 0
\begin{array}{ccc} \left|f(x)-f(a)\right| &=& \left|x\sin \frac1x-a\sin \frac1a\right| \\ &=& \left|x\sin \frac 1x-a\sin \frac 1x+a\sin \frac 1x-a\sin \frac1a\right| \\ &\le& \left|x-a\right|\left|\sin \frac 1x\right|+a\left|\sin \frac 1x-\sin \frac1a\right| \\ &<& \delta+a\left|\sin \frac 1x-\sin \frac1a\right| \end{array}
\begin{array}{ccc} \left|\sin \frac 1x-\sin \frac1a\right| &=& \left|2\sin \frac{\frac1x-\frac1a}{2}\cos\frac{\frac1x+\frac1a}{2} \right| \\ &=& 2\left|\sin \frac{x-a}{2xa}\cos\frac{x+a}{2xa} \right| \\ &\le&  2\left|\sin \frac{x-a}{2xa}\right|\end{array}
